### 2.6 Gap Analysis

The literature review reveals several unresolved challenges that motivated this work:

**Character Consistency:** No existing system provides multi-metric validation of character consistency across panels. Single-metric approaches fail to capture all dimensions of visual consistency, allowing color shifts, structural changes, and style variations to go undetected.

**Reference-Free Generation:** All systems require pre-generated character references or manual intervention. The bootstrap problem remains unsolved, limiting the automation and accessibility of comic generation systems.

**Speech Bubble Placement:** Automated layout algorithms frequently occlude faces or critical visual elements, particularly in complex scenes with multiple characters. The lack of robust collision avoidance limits the readability of AI-generated comics.

**Resource Optimization:** No system has been optimized for the T4 GPU, limiting accessibility. This work addresses this gap through comprehensive optimization strategies.

**Multi-Character Support:** Existing systems focus on single characters, failing to capture ensemble dynamics essential for cinematic storytelling.

