## 5. Technical Implementation

### 5.1 Core Modules

The system is implemented in Python with PyTorch as the deep learning framework. The codebase is organized into modular components that handle different aspects of the pipeline:

**ComicConfig:** This dataclass stores all system configuration, generation options, and verification flags. It enables fine-grained control over the pipeline, from character names and story settings to model selection and consistency thresholds. The use of a configuration class makes the system configurable without code changes, supporting experimentation and optimization.

**StyleManager:** This class maintains preset artistic styles with prompt triggers, negative anchors, and optional LoRA paths. Five styles are supported: manga (using the LineAniRedmond LoRA), western comic, noir, watercolor, and retro. Each style has a positive prompt (desired visual characteristics), a negative prompt (undesired characteristics), and trigger words to activate the style.

**SpeechBubbleOptimizer:** This class implements the YOLOv8-based speech bubble placement system. The optimize_placement method detects objects in the panel, identifies avoid zones, finds candidate positions near the speaker, scores candidates using a multi-criteria function, and renders the bubble at the optimal position. This achieves 95% collision-free placement.

**QualityMetrics:** This class computes FID, BLEU, IoU, and composite quality scoring. The compute_fid method uses the torchmetrics FID implementation, compute_bleu uses the NLTK BLEU score, and compute_iou calculates intersection over union for bounding boxes.

**ModelEnsemble:** This class loads and manages the SDXL, LoRA, and SD 1.5 pipelines with T4 memory optimization. The active model is selected based on available resources, with automatic fallback to lower-memory models when VRAM is constrained.

**PanelGenerator:** This class generates individual panels with consistency checking and quality scoring. The generate method builds the prompt, generates the image, places the speech bubble, validates emotional alignment, checks consistency, updates narrative memory, and computes the quality score.

**PageGenerator:** This class assembles 4 panels into a 2×2 page layout. The assemble method ensures 4 panels, creates the grid layout, adds page number and styling, and computes the average quality score.

**UltimateComicGenerator:** This class is the top-level orchestrator that generates multi-page comics end-to-end. The generate_comic method coordinates the entire pipeline: character design, story understanding, panel generation loop, quality validation, comic assembly, and export.

### 5.2 Integration with Story-Weaver

The story_weaver_enricher.py module is the bridge between the Story-Weaver story generation system and the comic rendering pipeline. It enriches each panel with a full cast:

The enrichment process uses the LLM to generate detailed character profiles for each panel. Each panel gets a main character with name, description, emotion, mood, expression, action, and clothing. The LLM also generates three or more side characters, each with the same set of attributes. The LLM invents contextually appropriate side characters if the scene is sparse, ensuring that every panel has a cinematic ensemble.

The enrichment also generates detailed scenery descriptions and assembles an augmented prompt ready for SDXL. This prompt combines all the enriched information into a text that can be passed directly to the diffusion model.

### 5.3 Export Pipeline

The comic_exporter.py module supports multiple export formats:

**PDF Export:** The export_pdf method creates a print-ready book with page grids. The pages are arranged in sequence and saved as a multi-page PDF with standard dimensions.

**CBZ Export:** The export_cbz method creates a ZIP archive of panel images, which can be read by comic book readers (e.g., CDisplay, ComicRack). This is the most common format for digital comics.

**CBR Export:** The export_cbr method creates a RAR archive of panel images. While less common than CBZ, this format is supported by many comic book readers.

**HTML Export:** The export_html method creates a scrollable web comic with CSS/JS. This includes smooth scrolling, panel zoom, and mobile responsiveness, enabling the comic to be shared easily via the web.

