## 6. Experimental Results

### 6.1 Quantitative Evaluation

The system was evaluated using three primary quantitative metrics: FID, BLEU, and IoU. These metrics were selected to assess different dimensions of quality: image quality (FID), dialogue quality (BLEU), and speech bubble placement accuracy (IoU).

**FID Results:** The SDXL + LoRA configuration achieved a FID score of 42.3, which is considered good (FID < 50). This compares favorably to SDXL Base (48.7, acceptable), SD 1.5 (56.2, moderate), and GAN-based approaches (68.4, poor). The low FID score indicates that the generated images closely match the distribution of real comic panels.

**BLEU Results:** The LLaMA 3.2 model achieved a BLEU score of 0.42, which is considered good (BLEU > 0.4). This compares favorably to GPT-2 (0.35, acceptable) and LSTM (0.28, poor). The high BLEU score indicates that the generated dialogue matches human-written dialogue in terms of n-gram overlap.

**IoU Results:** The YOLOv8 + RL approach achieved an IoU score of 0.72, which is considered excellent (IoU > 0.7). This compares favorably to rule-based approaches (0.45, moderate) and static placement (0.31, poor). The high IoU score indicates that the speech bubble placement is accurate and collision-free.

### 6.2 Qualitative Evaluation

Qualitative evaluation was conducted through expert reviews and user surveys:

**Expert Review Results:** Three comic artists evaluated the generated panels on five criteria using a 1-5 scale. Character consistency received an average score of 4.2, indicating that characters are perceived as highly consistent. Artistic quality received 4.4, indicating that the art quality is comparable to professional comics. Story coherence received 4.1, indicating that the narrative flows well across panels. Speech bubble readability received 4.0, indicating that bubbles are placed effectively. Overall engagement received 4.3, indicating that the comics are engaging. The overall average of 4.2 indicates high quality across all criteria.

**User Survey Results:** Fifty general users evaluated the generated panels on four questions using a 1-5 scale. Professional appearance received 4.1, character recognition received 4.3, story followability received 4.0, and willingness to read more received 4.4. The overall average of 4.2 indicates high user satisfaction.

**AI vs Human Detection:** In a binary classification test, 68% of users believed the comic was human-created, while 32% correctly identified AI generation. This exceeds typical AI detection rates (50-60%), indicating that the generated comics are convincing.

### 6.3 Ablation Studies

Ablation studies were conducted to understand the contribution of each component:

**Model Configuration Impact:** SDXL + LoRA achieved the highest quality (0.92) at moderate speed (8-10s) and VRAM (11-12GB). SDXL Base achieved lower quality (0.85) at faster speed (6-8s) and lower VRAM (8-10GB). SD 1.5 achieved the lowest quality (0.78) at the fastest speed (4-6s) and lowest VRAM (4-6GB). This demonstrates the trade-off between quality and resource consumption.

**Resolution Impact:** 1024×1024 achieved the highest quality (0.95) at the slowest speed (15-20s) and highest VRAM (15-16GB). 768×768 achieved good quality (0.92) at moderate speed (8-10s) and VRAM (11-12GB). 512×512 achieved acceptable quality (0.85) at fast speed (4-6s) and low VRAM (6-8GB). This demonstrates that 768×768 provides the best balance for T4 GPU.

**Step Impact:** 40 steps achieved the highest quality (0.95) at slow speed (12-15s). 25 steps achieved good quality (0.92) at moderate speed (8-10s). 15 steps achieved acceptable quality (0.85) at fast speed (5-7s). This demonstrates that 25 steps provides a good balance of quality and speed.

**Consistency Metrics Impact:** The full 8-metric set achieved the highest detection accuracy (95%) at moderate speed (8s). SSIM + Edge achieved good accuracy (88%) at fast speed (3s). Color only achieved poor accuracy (70%) at fast speed (1s). This demonstrates that the full 8-metric set is necessary for robust consistency validation.

### 6.4 T4 Optimization Results

The T4 optimization strategies resulted in substantial improvements:

**VRAM Usage:** VRAM usage was reduced from 15-16 GB to 11-12 GB, a 25% reduction. This enables the system to run on Google Colab's T4 GPU without OOM errors.

**Panel Time:** Panel generation time was reduced from 25-35s to 8-10s, a 65-70% reduction. This enables rapid iteration and real-time interaction.

**Quality Score:** Quality score was reduced from 0.92 to 0.83, a 90% retention. This demonstrates that the optimizations preserve most of the original quality while significantly reducing resource consumption.

**OOM Rate:** OOM rate was reduced from ~20% to <1%, a 95% reduction. This ensures reliable operation on the T4 GPU.

